  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2015_Solutions_2015s_page_005_3",
    "text": "To produce a value of n for which sn = 2015 (mod 10000), we take n = 3m + 1 for some nonnegative integer m for which 53m+1 = 30m + 15. We must also have 30m = 2000 (mod 10000), or equivalently m = 400 (mod 1000). By taking m = 1400, we ensure that m = 2 (mod 3), so Sm = 10m + 7; this ensures that Sn does indeed equal 30m + 15 = 42015, as desired.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1277153300739812,
      0.11185515889495615,
      0.49069406821482675,
