    "text": "On the other hand, we claim that if k > 1, then rik > 0 and uk > 0 if k is even, and tk > 0 and ruk > 0 if k is odd (in particular, uk can never be zero). The claim is true for k = 2 by the relation M7 = 2rM + 8s 1. Assuming the claim for k, and multiplying both sides of the relation Mk = 1M + uk| by M, yields",
